ol and will let you loot it instead of it rotting.  But do realize trains happen a lot with noobs pulling haha.  Got to be careful.  All pieces can be picked up pretty easy with a good puller.  Never compared it to crafted, but it's decent.  Once you get most of this armor, start getting the non Jarsarth slots filled up. (eg.  mask, cloak, neck, etc.)  That armor should carry you to planes level so all you would really have to concentrate on would be getting decent weapons.  Once you are ready to do planes, go get the new Legionaire stuff.  Legionaire has a little less AC but on an Iksar it's the equivalent of Indo with good resists and stats.  Also you can get PoG armor and do the quests from Velious.  In the 50+ range you'll also be getting some good weapons and stuff for your warrior through trades or by need before greed basis.  Just level up your Iksar and have fun.  In time everyone know why we are KOS everywhere,  It's because they fear the Iksar.<br>
<br>
Kazark Snaketongue, 56 Iksar Warrior<br>
